commit.message:
Fix for -Werror=range-loop-construct in GCC 11.

Range iteration in GCC 11 triggers range-loop-construct due to mismatch
between element types (const key) forcing a copy. Switch to const auto&
to avoid the type mismatch.
Fix overflow warnings (errors) in tests on 32bit builds.

Fix uninitialize variable in constexpr function warning.

Reported on g++ 6.4.0.

Avoid bounds checks on std::vector::operator[] in debug builds.

Some implementations of std add bounds checks to operator[] in
debug builds, even though is it specified to not perform bounds
checks and it is valid to use the address of the element one past
the end of an array in interator contexts.

Use pointer arithmetic on the value of std::vector::data() instead.
Fix call to Ensure in integer specialization of std::vector.

Remove Optional<std::initializer_list<int>> test.

Remove an invalid test that has a lifetime issue due to the init
list not copying the values of the internal array.

Issue detected by -fstack-protector.
docs: fix typo
Address minor incompatibility with constexpr in GCC 5.4.

Refactors and support for constexpr serialization.

- Remove total order of fields test for unbounded logical buffers;
  it is not possible to do this in standards-compliant way at this
  time. Replace with an explicit tag to enable unbounded operation.
- Clean up member pointer utilities to support constexpr contexts.
- Add constexpr serialization tests.
- Disable test coverage analysis by default in the makefile.
- Deprecate NOP_EXTERNAL_TEMPLATE, NOP_EXTERNAL_STRUCTURE can now
  handle un-elaborated template types as well.
Add detection trait utility.

Update buffer-oriented readers/writers and introduce new ones.

- Optimize BufferReader/BufferWriter to avoid unnecessary bounds
  checks and take advantage of compiler memcpy optimizations.
- Introduce PedanticBufferReader/PedanticBufferWriter that performs
  bounds checks on every operation to support mixed access patterns
  safely.
- Introduce ConstexprBufferWriter to support future constexpr
  serialization.
- Tweak BoundedReader/BoundedWriter to line up with other types.

Make more things constexpr-compatible.

Also clean up some header dependencies.
Change Status<T>::GetErrorMessage() to return const char*.
Fix bug in table entry size estimation.
Fix additional warnings from Clang 7.
Fix compilation with clang++-7.
Fixed Spelling.
Disable fallthrough attribute for gcc versions earlier than 7.0.0
Add support for later versions of GCC on Linux.
Aggressively constexpr everything to enable constexpr use cases.
Clean up old uses of template keyword that are unnecessary in C++14.
Add example of interfacing with python through a C ABI shared lib.
Simplify interface example with FdReader/FdWriter and constexpr dispatch.
Add FdReader and FdWriter utility types.

Add support for constexpr InterfaceBindings.

This makes it possible to create constexpr dispatch tables, including
as static constexpr auto members.
Add comments ErrorStatus with the numeric value of each enumerator.

Add support for C style structures with array of size 1 at the end.

- Add checks to ensure that the one-element array is the last member.
- Add checks that the value type of the array is trivially destructible.
- Allow arrays passing the checks to read and write past the end.
Add detection logic for gtest and disable building tests if not found.

Add support for value wrapper types with NOP_VALUE macro.

- Add facility and tests.
- Tweak macro names in other header files.

Switch to a platform-specific SizeType for container lengths.

The primarily avoids narrowing conversions from uint64_t to size_t
on 32bit platforms. The effect of this change is that 32bit
platforms generate early decode errors when handling containers
with element counts greater than 4GiB. This is unlikely to be a
problem given that 32bit platforms lack sufficient memory to
handle such sizes anyway.
